modules.description: Provides functions to parse and execute test cases from structured text files, including command execution, output comparison, and status verification. Works with strings, file paths, and shell command structures to validate CLI application behavior. Used to automate regression testing of command line tools by simulating user input and checking expected outputs.

Provides pretty-printing for commands, lines, and test structures, with options to filter output. Processes Cram test files, extracts specific parts, and compares output with wildcard support. Converts test data to strings, HTML, and executes test runs with custom processing.
